description:
When British S.A.S. commandos and a troop of mafia soldiers target Tommy Monaghan and his partner, Natt, they must stand side by side in a fight they cannot win. Then, Tommy and his comrades sign up for mercenary action in Africa against super-powered opponents. Collected from HITMAN #23-36 and 1,000,000.

Back Blurb

Over the years, hitman Tommy Monaghan has made his share of mistakes --- some worse than others. The lowlifes he normally takes on (super-villains, mobsters, other characters of low repute) aren't the most professional of adversaries, so he's usually been able to get by on his alien-enhanced abilities and razor-sharp shooting skills. But as good as Tommy may be, he's no match for the men of Great Britain's Special Air Service Regiment --- something that all of Gotham City is about to discover in a terrifyingly first-hand manner.

In the aftermath, Tommy and his partner, Natt the Hat, find themselves seriously questioning their career path. With work drying up at home (not to mention the inconvenience of an all-out mafia vendetta against them), a mercenary assignment in the African's wilderness seems like just the ticket. After all, what could possibly go wrong?

HITMAN creators Garth Ennis and John McCrea are joined by inkers Garry Leach and Andrew Chui for TOMMY'S HEROES, collecting issues 23-36 of the no-holds-barred series as well as the special issue #1,000,000 featuring Tommy's legendary journey to the 853rd century!
name: Volume 5

A special group of veterans is dispatched on their trail, with orders to remove them once and for all and prevent them from revealing the bloody covert ops campaign conducted by MBS in Latin America. But appearances can be deceiving, for the hunt for Pistoia's renegade Cyclops team is breaking all previous audience viewing records...

But when Zero crosses paths with an old adversary from the former Hammer Empire, will his thirst for revenge put Abbey in the middle of the crossfire? Find out as the year's most dangerous crossover event continues!

description: GUEST-STARRING HAWKEYE! The Avenger Hawkeye has followed the trail of destruction and ruined souls the Ghost Rider has left in its burning wake. And he isn't the only one with his sights set on the Spirit of Vengeance. The wild hunt for the Rider begins here.

Struggling to understand her connection to the vampyre goddess Nyx and her elemental affinities, Zoey Redbird's got her hands full at the House of Night. Add needing a plan to revamp the student group known as the Dark Daughters, and this third-former vampyre's in need of a hand. Turning to her friends, Zoey hopes to gain clarity in her quest to understand where she fits into the modern world of vampyrism.

Still trying to recover from the shock of his brother's death, Junya decides to follow in Ando's footsteps. First on the agenda is revenge on the ones who caused his brother's death. Can Junya succeed where Ando failed...?

Then, tragedy strikes Karasumori...

In the aftermath, restructuring at the Shadow Organization--the group charged with protecting humanity from dark magic--leads to a promotion for Yoshimori's elder brother. And then the boys' absentee mother turns up with a surprising agenda for both Yoshimori and the guardian of Karasumori!

1889, the steamship l'Anjou, on route from Murmansk to Le Havre, cruises amidst icebergs when a ship is sighted on a gigantic iceberg. The captain decides to send a lifeboat to examine the wreck. Six sailors, the first mate and Jérôme Plumier, passenger and medical student, are the boarding crew.

While onboard the wreck their vessel, l'Anjou, explodes leaving the lifeboat crew as sole survivors of this event.

name: The Palmer Addley Infection, Part 3

description:
The Immortal City has been destroyed and Issac Newton is on the lam. Da Vinci, Michelangelo, Nostradamus and the Eternal Dynamo need to make an impossible journey to stop him.

Tesla, Stark and Richards travel to the Zargos mountains to find the life-support pods where the three men of the Last Caliphate are in suspended animation. They are the embodiment of branching time and will travel with the others to the future. All except Leonardo get into position inside the Human Machine. Leonardo is the anchor, the sacrifice, the builder. As they travel we see episodes from Marvel history: SHIELD and Nick Fury, the X-Men, the Avengers, the Fantastic Four, the discovery of Captain America, the death of Jean Grey, the second generation of X-Men, Spider-Man, Magneto and the Kree-Skrull war. We also see the future, the ‘Days of Future Past’ reality, Hope Summers, Valeria Richards and the Ultron war future as seen in the Avengers.

2060: We see three versions of the future, where events happen in the same way but with a different environment: Paradise, the Height of Modernity and the End of the World. In all three, Tesla flies up to a tower and is blasted by Newton. In all three, Newton and the Celestial battle the others while Michelangelo prepares the Human Machine for its final task.
name: Chapter Four: All Together Now

description: With spell-crazed hit mages and the malevolent serpentine demon known as the Swordbreaker hot on his tail, it's a steep learning curve for the Occultist, who must master the powerful magic of the Sword-or suffer at the hands of numerous sorcerous enemies. But is our hero wielding this enigmatic weapon, or is it the one in control?

Orchid, Simon, and Yehzu meet a mysterious, forest-dwelling woman named Opal and hear the tale of General China's defeat at the hands of Tomo Wolfe. As Orchid struggles to find an outlet for her anger, Simon pleads for help from this experienced woman, whom he sees as a new and knowledgeable ally. Is this the turning point in the efforts of the uprising? Or another setback for a hopeless cause?

A special, silent Christmas story that reunites writer Tony Lee with The Time Machination's Paul Grist! When robots attack Santa in order to destroy Christmas, it's up to the Doctor to save the day! But when one of Santa's reindeer is injured, can the TARDIS manage to get to everyone's house over Christmas Eve?
name: Silent Knight

description: Patience and Kristof's quest to recover a piece of the One True Cross takes a deadly turn in Mexico. Will Patience be able to recover the familial relic or will this mission make her just another statistic in a long line of Magdalenas? Another issue of world-spanning
name: The One, True Cross, Part 2

description:
When a Boeing 777 lands at JFK International Airport and is unable to be opened, the Center for Disease Control is on first call but believes the situation might be too much for them to handle.

Assuming a possible terrorist attack, Dr. Ephraim Goodweather and his team of expert biological-threat are called into the scene, but what lies inside the airplane is much deeper and darker than anyone could have imagined.
'SIXTEEN' Kill or your best friends will murder you. What do you do? The stunning end of the first arc of PIGS by NATE COSBY (Jim Henson's Storyteller), BEN McCOOL (MEMOIR, CHOKER) & BRENO TAMURA.
name: Sixteen
